baseName.value: Hot-rolled reinforcing steel for concrete in bars and coils

generalComment.value:
Data quality has been assessed and validated during data collection process.


According to ISO 14040 and 14044, allocation is avoided whenever possible by dividing the system into subsystems. When allocation cannot be avoided physical properties are used to drive flow analysis.


According to EN:15804 the applied cut-off criterion for mass and energy flows is 1%.

technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesse.value: Bars: diameters from 6 mm to 32 mm, length up to 18 m, weight up to 2300 kg; Coils: diameters from 6 mm to 16 mm, weight from 1450 kg to 3000 kg

technologicalApplicability.value:
Hot rolled reinforcing steel for concrete in bars and coils
 Steel coming from post and pre consumer steel scraps produced in electric arc furnace route (EAF) and further hot rolling process
